During this course financial decisions at the investor as well as corporate level will be covered, including the following subjects: market efficiency, risk and return, portfolio theory, the concept of time value of money, analysis of different financial instruments (bonds, stocks), taxation of financial instruments, working capital management, capital structure and cost of capital, financial planning, capital budgeting, etc.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course provides basic knowledge about the main concept of financial management at corporate and investor level.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the successful completion of the course, students have acquired some basic knowledge about theoretical foundation of financial management including appropriate terminology; about the role of financial manager in a company; about the links between financial management and other disciplines and some proficiency how to apply the theory in practice, specifically how to use the concept of time value of money, how to evaluate investment projects and make financial projections, how to estimate the risk associated with different types of investments.
During this course students can acquired some experience how to use spreadsheet programs to solve basic financial problems in the field of financial management
